What is going on around him?

35
00:03:37,616 --> 00:03:39,316
Oh, all sorts of things.

36
00:03:39,814 --> 00:03:42,443
For example .. you.
- Me?

37
00:03:43,081 --> 00:03:45,926
Every morning you come
here and tidy up this room.

38
00:03:46,340 --> 00:03:47,812
Well, it needs a woman's touch.

39
00:03:48,027 --> 00:03:49,955
Yes, but who gets the credit for it?

40
00:03:50,349 --> 00:03:53,325
Me. He thinks I bring
him spring flowers.

41
00:03:54,030 --> 00:03:56,030
Flowers .. ha.

42
00:03:56,781 --> 00:03:59,532
I wonder what kind of
a man he thinks I am.

43
00:04:00,412 --> 00:04:02,881
The thing that makes history
interesting is the human element.

44
00:04:03,876 --> 00:04:07,248
It isn't so important to know that the
Battle of Philippi was fought in 42 B.C.

45
00:04:07,501 --> 00:04:09,004
As it is to know <i>why</i> it was fought.

46
00:04:10,646 --> 00:04:13,060
We have seen how, after
the Battle of Philippi ..

47
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:17,285
Antony and Octavius .. might have
divided the world between them.

48
00:04:18,434 --> 00:04:21,016
But Mark Antony felt that
his portion of the world ..

49
00:04:21,748 --> 00:04:23,335
Was well lost for love.

50
00:04:24,011 --> 00:04:26,339
At which point history becomes
very human indeed.

51
00:04:28,555 --> 00:04:31,372
But unfortunately, the great
romantics are seldom practical men.

52
00:04:31,953 --> 00:04:34,282
And in the end, Caesar
defeated Mark Antony.

53
00:04:34,779 --> 00:04:36,385
Both on land and on sea.

54
00:04:37,061 --> 00:04:38,667
As we shall see in our next lecture.

55
00:04:39,916 --> 00:04:42,292
But before I close .. I must read you ..

56
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:45,062
One of Antony's dying speeches.

57
00:04:45,447 --> 00:04:47,372
From Shakespeare's Antony and Cleopatra.

58
00:04:48,390 --> 00:04:50,118
I am dying, Egypt. Dying.

59
00:04:50,643 --> 00:04:52,625
Only I here importune death awhile.

60
00:04:53,244 --> 00:04:55,779
Until of many thousand
kisses the poor last ..??

61
00:04:56,756 --> 00:04:58,061
I lay upon my lips.

62
00:05:00,164 --> 00:05:02,991
You see, Antony had
fallen upon his sword ..

63
00:05:03,752 --> 00:05:05,263
So he should not be taken prisoner.

64
00:05:05,752 --> 00:05:07,884
And now he begs Cleopatra
to remember him ..

65
00:05:08,513 --> 00:05:10,226
As he had once been in her thoughts.

66
00:05:13,293 --> 00:05:14,654
That's all for today.

67
00:05:25,180 --> 00:05:26,739
Dr Dominik?

68
00:05:28,288 --> 00:05:29,030
