So exciting.

74
00:05:42,326 --> 00:05:44,054
That's very kind of you.

75
00:05:45,914 --> 00:05:47,284
Yes, let me see. There's ..

76
00:05:47,641 --> 00:05:50,665
There's Hinckel's Life of Mark Antony.
- How do you spell it, please?

77
00:05:51,181 --> 00:05:52,477
I'll write it down for you.

78
00:05:58,904 --> 00:05:59,853
There you are.

79
00:06:00,895 --> 00:06:02,642
You'll find it rather a complete work.

80
00:06:03,436 --> 00:06:05,873
Three volumes.
- They have it in the library?

81
00:06:06,258 --> 00:06:08,156
No. But I'll lend it to you.
I have it at home.

82
00:06:08,371 --> 00:06:09,301
Thank you.

83
00:06:10,755 --> 00:06:13,074
I could stop by your
cottage and pick it up.

84
00:06:13,450 --> 00:06:15,943
No, no, no. I'll bring
it to class tomorrow.

85
00:06:17,980 --> 00:06:20,722
Am I being an awful bother?
- Not at all.

86
00:06:22,468 --> 00:06:25,097
It will seem strange not to come
for your lectures anymore.

87
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:27,323
After next week.

88
00:06:27,643 --> 00:06:28,460
Yes.

89
00:06:29,427 --> 00:06:31,314
