91
00:06:36,413 --> 00:06:37,822
Oh, but you're not old.

92
00:06:38,037 --> 00:06:39,821
Hmm. It's nice of you to say so.

93
00:06:40,421 --> 00:06:42,271
No, but it makes me
feel old when I think ..

94
00:06:43,248 --> 00:06:45,783
When you first came
to us .. four years ago.

95
00:06:47,097 --> 00:06:48,083
A little girl.

96
00:06:48,928 --> 00:06:51,472
I wasn't a little girl. I was fifteen.

97
00:06:52,608 --> 00:06:55,491
Think of it .. an old woman of fifteen.

98
00:06:56,880 --> 00:06:58,580
I remember you as you looked then.

99
00:06:59,208 --> 00:07:01,002
You had a little what
do you call it, there.

100
00:07:01,217 --> 00:07:02,572
A spit curl.
- Yes.

101
00:07:03,801 --> 00:07:05,754
I was so proud of that spit curl.

102
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:10,045
I thought it made me
look .. sophisticated.

103
00:07:11,895 --> 00:07:12,975
Oh, funny.

104
00:07:14,036 --> 00:07:15,458
They all want to be grown-up.

105
00:07:16,421 --> 00:07:17,858
When there's so much time.

106
00:07:18,656 --> 00:07:20,196
But I am grown-up now.

107
00:07:21,220 --> 00:07:22,309
And after next week.

108
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:25,737
Will you miss me?

109
00:07:25,952 --> 00:07:28,751
What? Why yes of course, I'll miss ..

110
00:07:30,112 --> 00:07:32,516
I mean to say, I always miss
the graduating classes.

111
00:07:33,183 --> 00:07:34,737
Heavens. I have a faculty meeting.

112
00:08:03,095 --> 00:08:04,137
Marie.

113
00:08:07,742 --> 00:08:11,610
What's the matter with you? All you've
been doing is walking around in a daze.

114
00:08:12,634 --> 00:08:13,836
I'm sleepy.

115
00:08:14,784 --> 00:08:16,118
