Show it to us. Come on.

118
00:08:25,565 --> 00:08:27,067
It's a picture of a man.

119
00:08:39,586 --> 00:08:41,417
Oh .. my glasses.

120
00:08:43,639 --> 00:08:46,382
I can't see a thing without
my glasses, girls.

121
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:49,688
My glasses .. my glasses.

122
00:08:52,571 --> 00:08:54,505
Where are my glasses, young ladies?

123
00:08:54,975 --> 00:08:57,275
I can't see without my glasses.

124
00:08:57,669 --> 00:09:00,233
Here are your glasses, Frau Wimmer.
- Oh.

125
00:09:01,031 --> 00:09:01,801
Oh.

126
00:09:05,161 --> 00:09:06,043
Now.

127
00:09:07,499 --> 00:09:08,795
Who did that?

128
00:09:09,433 --> 00:09:11,320
Shush .. who did ..

129
00:09:16,710 --> 00:09:17,780
Shush.

130
00:09:21,489 --> 00:09:24,776
I shall report this entire dormitory.

131
00:09:25,274 --> 00:09:27,311
To the Herr Direktor.

132
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:38,018
Hello, Anna.
- Hello, Stefan.

133
00:09:38,331 --> 00:09:39,547
I was for you.
- Really?

134
00:09:39,947 --> 00:09:42,079
And I've been thinking about you.
- Have you, Stefan?

135
00:09:42,434 --> 00:09:44,142
I was selfish about this book business.

136
00:09:44,357 --> 00:09:46,242
There's as much of you
in it as there is of me.

137
00:09:46,492 --> 00:09:49,957
Oh, you needn't thank me, Stefan. I've
been so terribly happy working with you.

138
00:09:50,173 --> 00:09:50,840
Oh.

139
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:54,445
Well, now the book is finished I'm not
letting the partnership finish too.

140
00:09:55,554 --> 00:09:57,188
We've got to go on, Anna.

141
00:09:57,742 --> 00:09:59,798
There are other fields
to explore together.

142
00:10:02,277 --> 00:10:04,005
Meaning just what, Stefan?

143
00:10:04,662 --> 00:10:07,394
I mean that we should make our
partnership known to the world .. now.

144
00:10:08,709 --> 00:10:11,694
Will you let me put your
name with mine as co-author?

145
00:10:19,301 --> 00:10:20,766
I'm very grateful to you, Stefan.

146
00:10:21,554 --> 00:10:24,266
'Dominik and Mathe's World
History for Advanced Classes'.

147
00:10:24,481 --> 00:10:26,803
How does it sound?
- It sounds very generous.

148
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:30,296
But after all, what I've done
is of so little importance.

149
00:10:30,511 --> 00:10:33,187
Nonsense, Anna. It was you who
pushed me on and inspired me.

150
00:10:33,854 --> 00:10:36,002
I want you to share
in any glory there may be.

151
00:10:40,833 --> 00:10:42,110
Thank you, Stefan.

152
00:12:18,538 --> 00:12:20,773
You're uncommonly silent, Stefan.

153
00:12:22,689 --> 00:12:24,351
No, I was thinking.

154
00:12:24,774 --> 00:12:26,154
Next week's commencement.

155
00:12:26,685 --> 00:12:28,394
Some of these girls
won't be coming back.

156
00:12:29,557 --> 00:12:30,862
And I shall miss them.

157
00:12:31,153 --> 00:12:33,820
I'm always very sad at
commencement myself.

158
00:12:34,712 --> 00:12:37,754
A boy when he graduates,
is still just a boy.

159
00:12:38,618 --> 00:12:41,848
But a girl .. she shakes
herself and stands before you.

160
00:12:42,186 --> 00:12:43,905
As a full-fledged woman.

161
00:12:45,585 --> 00:12:46,487
Yes.

162
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:49,482
And you, my learned colleague?

163
00:12:50,352 --> 00:12:51,116
Huh?

164
00:12:51,566 --> 00:12:53,134
What are you thinking about?

165
00:12:53,670 --> 00:12:56,778
Oh .. my mind was .. far away.

166
00:12:57,773 --> 00:13:00,928
Dreaming of .. other spring.

167
00:13:01,783 --> 00:13:04,658
It is better that old men
should dream of spring ..

168
00:13:05,669 --> 00:13:06,934
Impersonally.

169
00:13:10,656 --> 00:13:13,151
Will we draw lots?
- Not me. I wouldn't dare.

170
00:13:13,366 --> 00:13:15,790
Oh, scary. Just the four of us then.

171
00:13:16,005 --> 00:13:17,632
And the one who loses has to ask him.

172
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:21,441
Come on, Marie.

173
00:13:23,013 --> 00:13:25,604
Oh, Marie's it.
- You have to go and ask him.

174
00:13:26,107 --> 00:13:27,898
Oh, but I can't.
- But you've got to.

175
00:13:28,113 --> 00:13:30,352
You took the dare.
- Go on. Be a sport.

176
00:13:32,127 --> 00:13:33,930
You said you would.
Go on, now.

177
00:13:35,911 --> 00:13:38,399
I tell you, schoolgirls
are fiendishly clever.

178
00:13:38,699 --> 00:13:41,814
They'll take every advantage
of a poor, defenceless professor.

179
00:13:42,029 --> 00:13:43,629
And twist him round their fingers.

180
00:13:44,220 --> 00:13:45,859
I'm sorry to interrupt, gentlemen.

181
00:13:46,361 --> 00:13:47,338
Well?

182
00:13:47,958 --> 00:13:49,901
Doctor Dominik, will you dance with me?

183
00:13:53,385 --> 00:13:54,967
I don't understand.

184
00:13:55,361 --> 00:13:56,141
I ..

185
00:13:56,995 --> 00:13:58,196
Will you dance with me?

186
00:13:59,371 --> 00:14:01,911
I'm afraid it's not customary.
Not customary at all.

187
00:14:02,534 --> 00:14:04,094
You should know that.

188
00:14:11,069 --> 00:14:12,177
I'm sorry.

189
00:14:24,062 --> 00:14:25,486
My dear fellow.

190
00:14:26,189 --> 00:14:29,091
Weren't you a trifle priggish just then?

191
00:14:29,786 --> 00:14:31,448
She shouldn't have done such a thing.

192
00:14:31,729 --> 00:14:33,729
You've hurt the poor child's feelings.

193
00:14:34,508 --> 00:14:36,865
After all .. I am the
director of the school.

194
00:15:37,396 --> 00:15:38,945
You might have waited for me.

195
00:15:40,241 --> 00:15:41,161
Shush.

196
00:15:46,648 --> 00:15:49,137
Marie isn't here.
- No, I don't think so.

197
00:15:54,235 --> 00:15:56,293
Oh, here she is.
- Alright, Marie?

198
00:15:56,631 --> 00:15:57,711
Yes, sir.

199
00:15:58,143 --> 00:16:00,039
What happened to her?

200
