00:16:56,962 --> 00:17:00,352
Guard. One, two, three, four, five.

213
00:17:01,235 --> 00:17:04,182
Lunge. One, hold, recover. One.

214
00:17:04,877 --> 00:17:06,850
Two calls. One. Assemble. One.

215
00:17:07,065 --> 00:17:08,802
What is it this time, Stefan?

216
00:17:09,234 --> 00:17:11,788
It's my fountain pen. I have
three, and I can never find one.

217
00:17:14,107 --> 00:17:16,099
Well ..
- In Classroom 'B'.

218
00:17:17,319 --> 00:17:19,797
Oh .. I shouldn't like to lose this.

219
00:17:20,012 --> 00:17:22,278
It's the one you gave me
at Christmas. I'm very fond of it.

220
00:17:23,301 --> 00:17:24,428
Thank you, Stefan.

221
00:17:26,448 --> 00:17:28,266
I don't know what I'd
do without you, Anna.

222
00:17:28,872 --> 00:17:30,430
I should never have a fountain pen.

223
00:17:30,834 --> 00:17:32,759
Or a handkerchief.
- Or remember to eat a meal.

224
00:17:33,153 --> 00:17:35,031
No .. or ever publish a book.

225
00:17:37,924 --> 00:17:40,722
Herr Direktor .. Herr Direktor.

226
00:17:41,595 --> 00:17:44,506
Something terrible has happened.
- Well, what is it?

227
00:17:44,722 --> 00:17:47,079
Well, wait just a moment
until I get my breath. I ..

228
00:17:47,294 --> 00:17:49,125
I ran all the way upstairs.

229
00:17:49,464 --> 00:17:51,849
Hadn't you better sit down?
- Oh, thank you. I ..

230
00:17:53,548 --> 00:17:54,957
I'm better now.

231
00:17:55,980 --> 00:17:58,806
It has to do with your class.
- Well, what is it?

232
00:17:59,286 --> 00:18:02,027
After the examination,
when the girls went out.

233
00:18:03,107 --> 00:18:05,878
I carried on a little
investigation of my own.

234
00:18:06,367 --> 00:18:08,047
In my classroom? How strange.

235
00:18:08,601 --> 00:18:11,522
Please forgive me. It's a
weakness, you must understand.

236
00:18:12,334 --> 00:18:16,466
During the examination I noticed the
girls were drawing cartoons of me.

237
00:18:16,681 --> 00:18:19,132
And passing them around under the desks.

238
00:18:19,423 --> 00:18:21,780
They always show me
with teeth like a horse.

239
00:18:26,546 --> 00:18:28,227
Did you find it in the wastebasket?

240
00:18:28,556 --> 00:18:30,717
I found something else
in the wastebasket.

241
00:18:30,932 --> 00:18:31,580
What?

242
00:18:31,795 --> 00:18:32,809
A love letter.

243
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:35,815
Oh, well after all, that's nothing.

244
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:39,570
Yes, but <i>what</i> a love letter.
It fairly scorched my fingers.

245
00:18:40,153 --> 00:18:41,993
Gussie, are you crazy?
One of my girls?

246
00:18:42,340 --> 00:18:44,087
Yes, one of your girls.

247
00:18:44,312 --> 00:18:46,457
Read it. It's disgraceful.

248
00:18:51,268 --> 00:18:52,981
'My one and only love'.

249
00:18:53,420 --> 00:18:55,098
Hmm .. starts well.

250
00:18:57,747 --> 00:18:59,315
Perhaps I shouldn't read any further.

251
00:18:59,991 --> 00:19:03,794
Perhaps it would be better if the
Herr Direktor .. read the rest himself.

252
00:19:04,141 --> 00:19:05,736
Oh, really. I don't see why I ..

253
00:19:06,093 --> 00:19:08,262
It's your duty as head of the school.

254
00:19:10,206 --> 00:19:11,173
Well.

255
00:19:12,938 --> 00:19:17,436
'I close my eyes to dream of our meeting
that afternoon on Castle Mountain'.

256
00:19:18,243 --> 00:19:19,277
Castle Mountain?

257
00:19:19,492 --> 00:19:21,520
Last week. The day of the school outing.

258
00:19:22,065 --> 00:19:23,567
But I don't understand it.

259
00:19:24,027 --> 00:19:26,337
While the girls and the
faculty were in the village.

260
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:29,286
This charming creature slipped
away from the others ..

261
00:19:29,577 --> 00:19:32,742
To meet some boy with whom
she had a rendezvous.

262
00:19:33,925 --> 00:19:35,127
Could that be true?

263
00:19:35,342 --> 00:19:37,127
Unfortunately, it looks that way.

264
00:19:38,103 --> 00:19:39,877
Any signature?
- No.

265
00:19:40,498 --> 00:19:42,104
The girl who wrote that letter ..

266
00:19:42,517 --> 00:19:45,906
Must be brought before
the faculty and punished.

267
00:19:46,986 --> 00:19:49,455
Have you a pin?
- No.

268
00:19:49,850 --> 00:19:51,775
Very well. I must manage like this.

269
00:19:52,526 --> 00:19:54,048
It is your responsibility.

270
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:58,095
To the trustees of our school
and the parents of our girls.

271
00:19:58,959 --> 00:20:02,386
I presume you'll let me know.
When the faculty meeting will be.

272
00:20:03,212 --> 00:20:05,653
Yes. Your handkerchief.
- Thank you.

273
00:20:11,492 --> 00:20:15,509
Last night I congratulated myself we had
reached the end of the year without ..

274
00:20:16,714 --> 00:20:18,542
Now this thing pops in our faces.

275
00:20:21,490 --> 00:20:24,195
If it's as serious as the letter shows,
do you think we can keep it quiet?

276
00:20:25,463 --> 00:20:26,815
With Gussie on the trail?

277
00:20:27,303 --> 00:20:30,261
And our delightful humanitarian,
the mathematics professor?

278
00:20:31,262 --> 00:20:34,022
No. They'll demand we make
an example of the girl.

279
00:20:35,853 --> 00:20:38,764
Do you recognize the writing?
- Let me see.

280
00:20:40,003 --> 00:20:40,970
Uh ..

281
00:20:42,050 --> 00:20:43,364
Hmm, I'm not sure.

282
00:20:43,759 --> 00:20:46,115
I've just been going over some
of the examination papers.

283
00:20:46,670 --> 00:20:47,913
But I don't think that ..

284
00:20:48,198 --> 00:20:49,887
I hate to do it, but I suppose we must.

285
00:20:56,275 --> 00:20:57,200
No.

286
00:20:59,872 --> 00:21:00,886
Here.

287
00:21:02,116 --> 00:21:03,694
No. It's like it.

288
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:06,775
But it isn't the same.

289
00:21:09,366 --> 00:21:11,451
Wait .. I think we have it.

290
00:21:15,055 --> 00:21:17,167
Marie Claudel? Oh, no.

291
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:19,730
Oh, no. She couldn't have done it.

292
00:21:23,129 --> 00:21:24,838
Marie Claudel? Are you sure?

293
00:21:27,157 --> 00:21:28,997
Yes. Yes, it's the same writing.

294
00:21:32,095 --> 00:21:33,259
Please send for her.

295
00:21:34,030 --> 00:21:36,960
One, two, three, four, five.

296
00:21:37,749 --> 00:21:39,279
Seek, lunge, recover.

297
00:21:39,514 --> 00:21:42,847
One, two, three, four, five, six.

298
00:21:43,242 --> 00:21:46,622
One, two, three, four, five, six.

299
00:21:47,298 --> 00:21:50,087
Guard. One, two, three, four.

300
00:21:50,744 --> 00:21:51,994
And advance, double.

301
00:21:52,209 --> 00:21:54,350
One and two, three and four.

302
00:21:54,631 --> 00:21:57,289
One and two, three and four. Two calls.

303
00:21:57,627 --> 00:22:00,931
One. Assemble. One, two, three, four.

304
00:22:01,809 --> 00:22:02,627
[ Whistle ]

305
00:22:03,723 --> 00:22:04,847
Marie Claudel?

306
00:22:06,678 --> 00:22:08,500
Report to the Herr Direktor's
office at once.

307
00:22:16,941 --> 00:22:18,311
Herr Direktor sent for me?

308
00:22:20,743 --> 00:22:21,673
Yes.

309
00:22:24,812 --> 00:22:26,290
Do you know why I sent for you?

310
00:22:26,661 --> 00:22:27,835
No, Herr Direktor.

311
00:22:28,492 --> 00:22:29,629
Think for a moment.

312
00:22:30,586 --> 00:22:31,882
Well, I've been thinking.

313
00:22:33,346 --> 00:22:37,008
Have you done nothing during the past
few days that is .. unworthy of you?

314
00:22:42,103 --> 00:22:43,577
What excuse have you to offer?

315
00:22:44,535 --> 00:22:47,181
We drew lots .. we meant no harm.

316
00:22:49,173 --> 00:22:51,474
Who drew lots?
- The girls.

317
00:22:52,244 --> 00:22:54,788
And the one who lost
had to ask you to dance.

318
00:22:56,395 --> 00:22:57,954
I .. I wanted to apologize.

319
00:22:58,471 --> 00:23:00,405
Oh, that? That incident's forgotten.

320
00:23:01,194 --> 00:23:03,062
Then why did you send
for me, Herr Direktor?

321
00:23:08,151 --> 00:23:09,719
Do you recognize this writing?

322
00:23:11,419 --> 00:23:13,400
No.
- Look at it carefully.

323
00:23:16,293 --> 00:23:18,237
Where did you get it?
- Never mind that.

324
00:23:19,232 --> 00:23:20,659
Did you write it, yes or no?

325
00:23:22,922 --> 00:23:24,030
No, I did not.

326
00:23:25,167 --> 00:23:27,905
I want the truth.
- I did not write it.

327
00:23:31,029 --> 00:23:33,911
This writing checks, letter for letter,
with your examination paper.

328
00:23:35,592 --> 00:23:37,048
But I did not write it.

329
00:23:40,175 --> 00:23:41,433
Sit down.

330
00:23:46,674 --> 00:23:48,296
I'm going to dictate something to you.

331
00:23:55,024 --> 00:23:56,218
'My one and only love'.

332
00:23:56,721 --> 00:23:57,567
Oh, please.

333
00:23:57,995 --> 00:23:58,678
Write.

334
00:24:07,138 --> 00:24:10,114
'I think of nothing but that beautiful
moment when you held me in your arms'.

335
00:24:14,062 --> 00:24:15,596
I order you to write, Marie.

336
00:24:15,904 --> 00:24:16,782
Oh, I can't.

337
00:24:17,436 --> 00:24:18,885
Oh, please don't make me.

338
00:24:20,611 --> 00:24:21,953
Then you did write this?

339
00:24:23,493 --> 00:24:24,366
Yes.

340
00:24:25,784 --> 00:24:27,155
Oh, I'm so ashamed.

341
00:24:30,723 --> 00:24:32,141
How could it have happened?

342
00:24:32,376 --> 00:24:35,277
Surely you don't believe that
anything like that really happened?

343
00:24:36,854 --> 00:24:38,178
Then why did you write this?

344
00:24:40,234 --> 00:24:42,187
Well, it isn't a real letter.

345
00:24:42,816 --> 00:24:44,187
What is it then?

346
00:24:46,697 --> 00:24:48,294
How can I explain it to you?

347
00:24:49,561 --> 00:24:52,031
Well, here inside these walls.

348
00:24:52,726 --> 00:24:54,087
I'm still a schoolgirl.

349
00:24:55,430 --> 00:24:56,960
But the moment I step outside.

350
00:24:58,444 --> 00:25:01,365
I feel life around me.
I'm with the world.

351
00:25:02,576 --> 00:25:04,360
I feel like other people.

352
00:25:04,970 --> 00:25:06,350
Dream like other people.

353
00:25:07,514 --> 00:25:08,960
Then, I am not a schoolgirl.

354
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:11,439
I'm a human being.

355
00:25:13,327 --> 00:25:16,031
But this .. this isn't something
out of your imagination.

356
00:25:16,472 --> 00:25:17,486
It's real.

357
00:25:20,331 --> 00:25:21,881
Well, the letter is real.

358
00:25:22,632 --> 00:25:24,115
But what it says is not.

359
00:25:26,059 --> 00:25:27,900
The only true thing about it.

360
00:25:29,956 --> 00:25:31,562
Is that I am in love.

361
00:25:33,676 --> 00:25:34,822
Yes?

362
00:25:35,648 --> 00:25:36,684
And in my dreams.

363
00:25:37,257 --> 00:25:40,196
I've been in the embrace of the
man I love. Yes, that's the truth.

364
00:25:40,740 --> 00:25:42,073
But what you accuse me of ..

365
00:25:43,256 --> 00:25:44,393
I'm not guilty.

366
00:25:45,820 --> 00:25:47,003
And who is the man?

367
00:25:49,716 --> 00:25:50,952
Don't ask me that.

368
00:25:51,299 --> 00:25:52,998
You must tell me.
Who is the man?

369
00:25:54,002 --> 00:25:55,983
But I can't answer.
- Very well.

370
00:25:56,885 --> 00:25:59,073
I shall take your refusal
to answer as a confession.

371
00:26:00,903 --> 00:26:03,626
You will appear before a
faculty meeting at .. 5:30.

372
00:26:25,909 --> 00:26:27,994
We all know why this
conference has been called.

373
00:26:28,379 --> 00:26:31,909
By the rules, any member of the faculty
can demand investigation of a student ..

374
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:34,304
Accused of a serious irregularity.

375
00:26:35,891 --> 00:26:38,190
Frau Professor Wimmer
has made that demand.

376
00:26:39,542 --> 00:26:41,730
And I agree entirely
with Professor Wimmer.

377
00:26:42,387 --> 00:26:44,998
Too bad you two didn't
meet 20 years ago.

378
00:26:45,533 --> 00:26:47,383
I beg your pardon?
- Gentlemen, please.

379
00:26:48,898 --> 00:26:51,227
I prefer not to take any
part of this investigation.

380
00:26:51,452 --> 00:26:53,292
I'm only here to see
that justice is done.

381
00:26:53,846 --> 00:26:56,372
First I shall ask for a
report on Marie Claudel.

382
00:27:00,139 --> 00:27:02,318
For the years 1935 and 1936.

383
00:27:02,844 --> 00:27:05,351
Marie Claudel has stood
very high in her classes.

384
00:27:05,698 --> 00:27:08,731
We are not here to judge
Marie Claudel's education.

385
00:27:09,312 --> 00:27:10,392
It's her morals.

386
00:27:10,805 --> 00:27:13,857
Shall we hang the girl,
or just have her beheaded?

387
00:27:14,298 --> 00:27:17,913
We all know you've never been much
of a success in maintaining discipline.

388
00:27:18,344 --> 00:27:20,579
Your wife must treat you very badly.

389
00:27:21,081 --> 00:27:21,725
What?

390
00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:24,420
I've observed that teachers
who are browbeaten at home ..

391
00:27:24,635 --> 00:27:26,748
Are inclined to take
their revenge in school.

392
00:27:27,088 --> 00:27:29,273
Please. Let's not make
this a personal thing.

393
00:27:29,499 --> 00:27:32,390
Thank you for your protection,
Herr Direktor, but I don't need it.

394
00:27:32,935 --> 00:27:34,654
Attacks like that can't hurt me.

395
00:27:35,471 --> 00:27:37,490
I'll admit that my wife
is severe with me.

396
00:27:37,734 --> 00:27:39,415
But I am also severe with her.

397
00:27:39,950 --> 00:27:41,443
We are a severe family.

398
00:27:42,326 --> 00:27:46,195
Our severity towards the world springs
from our own strong convictions.

399
00:27:46,973 --> 00:27:49,416
I thought it sprang from
the .. gallbladder.

400
00:27:52,082 --> 00:27:53,904
I don't care to answer that.

401
00:27:55,763 --> 00:27:56,702
Go on, please.

402
00:27:57,951 --> 00:28:00,073
Well after all, we
only have this letter.

403
00:28:00,299 --> 00:28:03,632
We have no actual proof that Marie
Claudel is guilty of any wrongdoing.

404
00:28:03,923 --> 00:28:06,627
I object to the way you are
beating around the bush.

405
00:28:07,068 --> 00:28:09,244
Will Herr Doctor Spindler
kindly tell us exactly ..

406
00:28:09,459 --> 00:28:11,866
How you would like this
investigation conducted?

407
00:28:12,195 --> 00:28:14,091
Have you sent for her parents?
- No.

408
00:28:14,861 --> 00:28:17,922
And why not, may I ask?
- The girl has no father.

409
00:28:18,880 --> 00:28:21,266
Her mother is a hopeless invalid
in a sanatorium at HÃ¶flingen.

410
00:28:21,481 --> 00:28:24,016
I suppose that is intended
to prey upon our sympathies.

411
00:28:24,368 --> 00:28:27,960
I don't believe the girl is guilty of
anything but writing a silly love note.

412
00:28:28,495 --> 00:28:30,553
And it was her own private possession.

413
00:28:30,768 --> 00:28:33,887
If anyone is guilty, it's the person who
fished the letter from the wastebasket.

414
00:28:34,102 --> 00:28:35,233
If that is intended ..

415
00:28:35,448 --> 00:28:37,465
Anyone who pokes around
in the garbage can ..

416
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:40,406
Shouldn't be surprised
when he finds garbage.

417
00:28:40,673 --> 00:28:42,673
So <i>I</i> am the one to be insulted?

418
00:28:43,077 --> 00:28:47,471
Instead of throwing out the girl
who has contaminated our school.

419
00:28:48,339 --> 00:28:50,108
She could scarcely contaminate anyone.

420
00:28:50,756 --> 00:28:52,540
In two days she's graduating.

421
00:28:52,963 --> 00:28:56,474
Apparently the Herr Direktor is more
interested in the girl than the school.

422
00:28:56,925 --> 00:29:00,070
It will be a reflection on the school
if she's expelled before graduating.

423
00:29:00,539 --> 00:29:05,460
If I have anything to say to it,
she will <i>not</i> be allowed to graduate.

424
00:29:05,835 --> 00:29:08,277
Well, you talk about this girl
as if she were a criminal.

425
00:29:08,671 --> 00:29:12,962
The letter admits she had a rendezvous
with a man on .. Castle Mountain.

426
00:29:13,563 --> 00:29:15,704
What more do you want?
A photograph?

427
00:29:16,117 --> 00:29:18,333
Well after all, she's 19 years old.

428
00:29:18,746 --> 00:29:20,725
At that age, my mother
already had two children.

429
00:29:20,940 --> 00:29:22,173
Not in school.

430
00:29:22,399 --> 00:29:25,442
Nature doesn't care anything
about the location.

431
00:29:26,447 --> 00:29:28,888
You're just trying to keep us
from questioning the girl.

432
00:29:29,174 --> 00:29:30,590
We won't hinder you any further.

433
00:29:30,821 --> 00:29:32,981
Since you insist, you can begin
the inquisition yourself.

434
00:29:33,298 --> 00:29:33,942
Toni.

435
00:29:37,106 --> 00:29:38,773
Please ask Marie Claudel to come in.

436
00:29:39,294 --> 00:29:40,223
Just a moment.

437
00:29:41,481 --> 00:29:45,397
Have you ever noticed any boys hanging
around outside, waiting for the girls?

438
00:29:46,843 --> 00:29:48,026
Well, yes.

439
00:29:48,636 --> 00:29:52,402
There's one good-looking young fellow
that waits every day at the corner.

440
00:29:52,618 --> 00:29:54,947
Uhuh .. and do you know
for whom he waits?

441
00:29:55,162 --> 00:29:58,345
Certainly.
For Frau Professor Wimmer.

442
00:29:59,585 --> 00:30:02,148
You idiot.
That's my nephew.

443
00:30:02,562 --> 00:30:04,750
Well, I didn't say he
was your sweetheart.

444
00:30:06,797 --> 00:30:08,497
Now, now. Gentlemen, please.

445
00:30:13,154 --> 00:30:14,834
They want you, Mademoiselle.

446
00:30:16,243 --> 00:30:18,881
Don't worry. They can't eat you.

447
00:30:42,023 --> 00:30:43,535
Will you come over here, please?

448
00:30:48,785 --> 00:30:52,043
Certain members of the faculty
wish to ask you some questions.

449
00:30:54,663 --> 00:30:55,686
Dr Spindler?

450
00:30:57,245 --> 00:30:58,503
Come here.

451
00:31:00,635 --> 00:31:01,640
Closer.

452
00:31:02,309 --> 00:31:03,810
You're 19 years old?
- Yes, sir.

453
00:31:04,025 --> 00:31:05,466
French, aren't you?
- Yes, sir.

454
00:31:05,790 --> 00:31:07,681
Fond of the company of
young men, I presume?

455
00:31:08,053 --> 00:31:10,579
Do you enjoy dancing?
- Just as any girl.

456
00:31:11,189 --> 00:31:13,443
Are you wearing perfume?
- No, sir.

457
00:31:13,725 --> 00:31:15,236
Don't lie. I can smell it.

458
00:31:15,652 --> 00:31:17,869
You are aware that perfume
is not allowed in this school.

459
00:31:18,084 --> 00:31:19,739
It's not perfume.
- What is it then?

460
00:31:19,954 --> 00:31:20,624
Soap.

461
00:31:20,934 --> 00:31:23,246
So .. you washed with perfumed soap?

462
00:31:23,461 --> 00:31:25,425
I can't see that that
question belongs here.

463
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:28,092
It belongs in the analysis
of the girl's character.

464
00:31:28,731 --> 00:31:29,980
Give me your handkerchief.

465
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:33,081
Frau Professor, will you ..?
- I'm here.

466
00:31:34,311 --> 00:31:35,316
Wet your lips.

467
00:31:35,662 --> 00:31:37,389
If you please, I ..
- Wet your lips.

468
00:31:41,707 --> 00:31:44,214
Ah .. lip rouge.

469
00:31:44,622 --> 00:31:46,482
I think we have a rule about that.

470
00:31:46,697 --> 00:31:48,537
Please get on with your questioning.

471
00:31:50,557 --> 00:31:52,380
Do you remember the
school outing last week?

472
00:31:52,740 --> 00:31:53,951
Yes.
- What day was it?

473
00:31:54,639 --> 00:31:55,426
I'm not ..

474
00:31:55,641 --> 00:31:57,721
You do recall being in the
village with the others?

475
00:31:57,936 --> 00:31:58,553
Yes.

476
00:31:58,849 --> 00:32:01,409
Did you once leave the other girls?
- Well, I ..

477
00:32:01,624 --> 00:32:03,382
Tell the truth.
- Then give me a chance.

478
00:32:03,597 --> 00:32:05,721
Don't dare address me
in that tone of voice.

479
00:32:06,313 --> 00:32:08,980
Were you or were you not absent
at any time from the others?

480
00:32:10,389 --> 00:32:12,642
Well, yes .. I took a walk.

481
00:32:13,506 --> 00:32:15,553
Ah .. she took a walk.

482
00:32:16,248 --> 00:32:18,615
On Castle Mountain, wasn't it?
- Yes.

483
00:32:19,488 --> 00:32:21,704
And you were with a man there?
- No.

484
00:32:22,174 --> 00:32:24,596
You did not meet a man
on Castle Mountain?

485
00:32:24,916 --> 00:32:27,113
Herr Doctor Spindler,
your attitude isn't helping any.

486
00:32:27,347 --> 00:32:31,038
Since you refuse to answer, I shall tell
you what happened on Castle Mountain.

487
00:32:31,329 --> 00:32:34,136
I shall reconstruct
your little adventure.

488
00:32:34,868 --> 00:32:37,579
You slipped away from the rest of the
girls because you had a rendezvous.

489
00:32:37,881 --> 00:32:38,782
That's untrue.

490
00:32:38,997 --> 00:32:40,773
You met him in the forest.
In the shadows.

491
00:32:41,176 --> 00:32:42,903
Where you felt safe from prying eyes.

492
00:32:43,526 --> 00:32:45,179
You were alone in the forest.

493
00:32:45,742 --> 00:32:46,878
Alone with a man.

494
00:32:47,803 --> 00:32:50,076
And all about you the soft,
sweet smell of spring.

495
00:32:50,304 --> 00:32:50,890
No.

496
00:32:51,166 --> 00:32:52,783
He held you in his arms. He kissed you.

497
00:32:52,998 --> 00:32:54,898
Stop! I won't listen to you.

498
00:32:55,433 --> 00:32:57,254
What?
- I hate you.

499
00:32:57,649 --> 00:32:59,518
Every girl in this school hates you.

500
00:32:59,733 --> 00:33:03,310
You've always picked on me.
You, you filthy old pig.

501
00:33:03,705 --> 00:33:05,591
I don't blame her.
- Now, here, here.

502
00:33:05,807 --> 00:33:08,943
I demand she apologize.
- You brought it on yourself.

503
